  "text": "The Chromium renderer process sandbox implementation is structured across multiple components:\n\n1. **Linux seccomp-BPF Base Policy** (`sandbox/policy/linux/bpf_base_policy_linux.h`, `bpf_base_policy_linux.cc`): The `BPFBasePolicy` class (defined in `bpf_base_policy_linux.h`) implements the base seccomp-BPF sandbox policy for Linux. It inherits from `bpf_dsl::Policy` and provides the kernel attack surface reduction layer. The class implements `EvaluateSyscall()` and `InvalidSyscall()` methods to control syscall behavior. The `BPFBasePolicy::GetFSDeniedErrno()` static method returns EPERM as the error code for denied filesystem access.\n\n2. **Windows Sandbox Policy** (`sandbox/win/src/sandbox_policy.h`): The `TargetPolicy` class defines the Windows sandbox policy configuration interface. It works in conjunction with `TargetConfig` to configure sandbox parameters including token levels, job object settings, handle closures, file access rules, and registry access. The policy is applied to target processes before they enter lockdown mode.\n\n3. **Sandbox Type Definitions** (`sandbox/policy/mojom/sandbox.mojom`): The `Sandbox` enum defines all sandbox types including `kRenderer`, `kGpu`, `kService`, `kUtility`, `kNetwork`, `kNoSandbox`, and many others. This mojom interface serves as the contract for mojo services to specify which sandbox they should run in.\n\n4. **Renderer Process Sandbox Configuration** (`content/browser/renderer_host/renderer_sandboxed_process_launcher_delegate.h`, `renderer_sandboxed_process_launcher_delegate.cc`): The `RendererSandboxedProcessLauncherDelegate` class configures sandbox parameters for renderer process launch. The `GetSandboxType()` method returns `sandbox::mojom::Sandbox::kRenderer`. For Windows, the `RendererSandboxedProcessLauncherDelegateWin` subclass implements `InitializeConfig()` to configure renderer-specific mitigations including dynamic code disable for jitless renderers and app container policies.\n\n5. **Linux Sandbox Policy Selector** (`sandbox/policy/linux/sandbox_seccomp_bpf_linux.h`, `sandbox_seccomp_bpf_linux.cc`): The `SandboxSeccompBPF` class provides the central API for Linux sandbox management. The static method `PolicyForSandboxType()` takes a `sandbox::mojom::Sandbox` type and options, and returns a `std::unique_ptr<BPFBasePolicy>` appropriate for that sandbox type. This method maps each sandbox type to its corresponding policy implementation (e.g., `RendererProcessPolicy`, `GpuProcessPolicy`, `NetworkProcessPolicy`, etc.). The function also handles platform-specific variations (ChromeOS AMD/Intel/NVIDIA/ARM GPU policies) and is responsible for orchestrating the seccomp-BPF sandbox engagement for different process types."
}

